1
00:00:00,710 --> 00:00:04,040
Mom, we finally have a chance
to bring Chae Hwa Young down.

2
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:05,980
How?

3
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:09,580
I think Chae Hwa Young and Kang Jun Ho
are secretly looking for an investor.

4
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:11,280
- An investor?
- Yes.

5
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:14,620
So I came up with a little plan.

6
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,720
- Mom.
- Ma'am.

7
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:18,060
Come on.

8
00:00:20,490 --> 00:00:22,090
- Mom!
- Ma'am.

9
00:00:25,330 --> 00:00:27,970
Mom, it's me, Tae Pyung.

10
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:29,570
Tae Pyung.

11
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,240
Tae Pyung.

12
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:38,880
Baek Ho, thank you so much, too.

13
00:00:39,940 --> 00:00:42,910
I can't tell you how grateful I am...

14
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:45,580
for you loving and cherishing Jang Mi.

15
00:00:46,220 --> 00:00:49,220
- Thank you. I appreciate it, ma'am.
- Mom,

16
00:00:49,820 --> 00:00:51,090
do you only have eyes for Baek Ho?

17
00:00:51,620 --> 00:00:53,730
I was really moved.

18
00:00:54,790 --> 00:00:57,000
Of course, my dear Tae Pyung.

19
00:01:00,330 --> 00:01:04,600
I feel like Seo Rin woke me up
for a reason.

20
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:10,040
It's like she's telling me to make
Chae Hwa Young suffer the way she did.

21
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:12,810
Mom, is that really you?

22
00:01:14,010 --> 00:01:16,980
- It's strange hearing you talk like this.
- Tae Pyung.

23
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:21,450
Mom being okay has to be a secret
until we take down Chae Hwa Young.

24
00:01:21,690 --> 00:01:25,020
- Don't tell Tae Sook either, okay?
- Of course not.

25
00:01:25,290 --> 00:01:27,630
Baek Ho, you know I can keep a secret,
right?

26
00:01:32,830 --> 00:01:35,770
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

27
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:39,270
Wait, so we're making a plan
to take down Chae Hwa Young?

28
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,510
Yes.

29
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:44,140
It seems she plans to acquire Hills Hotel
using a slush fund.

30
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,280
Acquire it with a slush fund?

31
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:50,450
Then it seems she'll create her own hotel
called Dream Hills.

32
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:54,390
So that's her scheme
to break off from Dream Group.

33
00:01:54,450 --> 00:01:58,990
That's right. She'll acquire Hills Hotel
behind his back, expand it,

34
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:01,530
and then eventually partner
with Dream Group...

35
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:03,530
to completely take it over.

36
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:06,630
But does Chae Hwa Young
even have that kind of money?

37
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,000
She's not planning to buy the hotel
entirely with her own money.

38
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:12,300
I think she plans to find a major investor
to fund the acquisition.

39
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:16,040
- We have to stop her before that happens.
- So what we need to do now...

40
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:20,210
is bring in a big-shot investor
whom Chae Hwa Young can't resist.

41
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:22,650
Of course, the investor will be a fake.

42
00:02:22,950 --> 00:02:25,420
But it has to be someone
who can fool Chae Hwa Young completely.

43
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:29,190
That's how we'll make her cough up
that slush fund she's been hiding.

44
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:31,920
I'd like to be the one to do it.

45
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:36,930
Is there a high-profile female investor
around my age?

46
00:02:37,130 --> 00:02:39,230
Funny you should ask,
I've already found someone.

47
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:42,170
Back when I was working part-time
at a K-pop concert,

48
00:02:42,170 --> 00:02:44,170
I happened to help someone out.

49
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:48,940
Turns out she was a major female investor
from India, Chairman Ali.

50
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,310
How suffocating.

51
00:02:57,050 --> 00:02:58,920
How am I supposed to butter her up?

52
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:01,590
Who are you trying to butter up?

53
00:03:01,650 --> 00:03:04,220
Chairman Ali understands
every word you're saying.

54
00:03:07,530 --> 00:03:09,730
Let's just start with a slap.

55
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,500
My goodness!

56
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,070
How dare you hit me!

57
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:19,170
I'm a huge K-drama fan.

58
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,570
What you just said was about me, right?

59
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:25,040
No, wait, that's not what I meant.

60
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,280
The CEO of Dream Hotel is so classless.

61
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,550
Tommy, let's go to another hotel.

62
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:38,690
- Tommy, to the lobby.
- Yes, ma'am.

63
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:45,730
Chairman, I'm so sorry.

64
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,800
Please, you can't leave.

65
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:53,710
Chairman, please! Chairman Ali!

66
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:56,110
Chairman.

67
00:03:59,140 --> 00:04:00,310
I am truly sorry.

68
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:04,220
But I wasn't referring to you earlier.

69
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,320
Please, don't misunderstand, Chairman Ali.

70
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:10,990
A classless hotel with classless service.
I'm offended.

71
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:13,660
Get out of the way.
Chairman Ali is furious.

72
00:04:13,660 --> 00:04:15,060
Please, forgive me, just this once.

73
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,560
I'll do everything I can
to make your stay perfect.

74
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:21,770
Is this how you ask for forgiveness?
Don't you even watch K-Dramas?

75
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,870
- What?
- What are you doing?

76
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:25,400
Get on your knees, now!

77
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:28,670
You want me to kneel?

78
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:31,280
Tommy, this isn't working.

79
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:34,980
- Let's find another hotel.
- No, wait! Yes, I'll kneel.

80
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:40,650
No, please.

81
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:47,390
Chairman. I was truly wrong.
Please forgive me just this once.

82
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,160
Please, don't stay at another hotel.

83
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,060
Please stay at our hotel.

84
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:54,330
I'll ensure
you're treated with great respect.

85
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:56,030
What are your orders, Chairman?

86
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:00,100
I can't forgive you.

87
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:02,770
I wish I could just...

88
00:05:02,910 --> 00:05:05,010
No. There's too much money at stake.

89
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:08,310
I have to land her for Dream Hills,
no matter what it takes.

90
00:05:08,410 --> 00:05:09,480
Let's go, Tommy.

91
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:14,050
No, Chairman!

92
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,590
Excuse me, Chairman.

93
00:05:18,590 --> 00:05:21,990
My apologies. I'm Director Ma Seo Rin.

94
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:26,030
Director Ma Seo Rin?

95
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:28,730
What do you mean you're leaving our hotel?

96
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,540
If you could tell me what happened,

97
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:35,340
I'll make sure we resolve the issue
to your satisfaction.

98
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:38,780
That woman is rude.
And now the Chairman is furious.

99
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:41,110
That woman is so vulgar.

100
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:43,210
She said she was going to cook and eat me.

101
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:46,580
She eats people? My goodness.

102
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,150
This is horror.

103
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:52,120
Ms. Chae Hwa Young, is that true?

104
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:56,290
- No, that's not what...
- We haven't trained our staff properly.

105
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:59,060
- Please forgive us.
- An employee?

106
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:01,470
Isn't she the CEO?

107
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:06,370
That woman's a liar.

108
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:09,340
Tommy, we're going to another hotel.

109
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:13,910
Why did you tell her you were the CEO?
Seriously.

110
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:15,410
Jin Hong Ju, don't mess with me right now.

111
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,850
She's not the CEO,
just a member of the staff.

112
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:22,590
She must have misspoken
when she introduced herself in English.

113
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,020
Please forgive her.

114
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:27,460
- It's our fault.
- Enough.

115
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,490
Tommy, let's find another hotel.

116
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,560
Wait, Chairman!

117
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:36,030
When we heard you were coming,
we prepared a special K-drama tour.

118
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:39,440
And some of your favorite actors
will be there.

119
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,570
We'll save you VIP seats.

120
00:06:41,570 --> 00:06:43,410
- How does that sound?
- Goodness!

121
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,710
Tour service...

122
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:48,410
I like the sound of that, Director Ma.

123
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:51,950
Also, we'll have another concierge
assigned to you.

124
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,790
Or if you'd prefer,
I can personally attend to you.

125
00:06:54,990 --> 00:06:56,220
That sly fox...

126
00:06:56,650 --> 00:06:57,920
She thinks she can just swoop in
like that?

127
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:01,630
No way. I have to win that Chairman over,
whatever it takes.

128
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:03,730
Chairman Ali.

129
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:08,070
Please give me one more chance.
I promise I'll take excellent care of you.

130
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,700
Just one more chance, please.

131
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:16,310
Okay. If our job is to grant the wishes
of the living,

132
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,910
then we can grant the wishes of the dead,
can't we?

133
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:23,180
That's a line you hear in K-dramas
all the time, right?

134
00:07:23,410 --> 00:07:24,420
Right?

135
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,750
The dead?

136
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,240
Again, I am so sorry
for earlier, Chairman.

137
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:47,040
Whatever you need, just ask.

138
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:50,410
I will provide you with service
that's guaranteed to satisfy.

139
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:54,650
Here, why don't you start
with a welcome drink?

140
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:04,520
- What? What's wrong now?
- Your welcome is a complete disaster.

141
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,420
That's why the Chairman is angry.

142
00:08:07,730 --> 00:08:09,630
Hurry up and take off
Chairman Ali's shoes.

143
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:11,860
Excuse me?

144
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,330
- What is it now?
- Shoes.

145
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:28,880
Is there anything else I can do for you?

146
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:30,480
Our Dream Hotel...

147
00:08:30,850 --> 00:08:33,080
- is the finest hotel in Korea...
- Tommy.

148
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:36,720
This place is a joke.
She refuses to do shoe duty?

149
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:39,790
My goodness, Tommy!

150
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:41,490
(Get lost!)

151
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,700
What in the world is she saying?

152
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,400
Alright.

153
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,030
"Atithi Devo Bhava..."

154
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,470
means to treat a guest
as if they were a deity...

155
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:55,070
and to purify and bless them.

156
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,910
So that's the meaning behind
the foot-washing ceremony, right?

157
00:08:58,210 --> 00:09:00,110
Exactly. It's one of their traditions.

158
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:01,610
I've got a lot to learn.

159
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,980
I'll be sure to memorize it all.

160
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,490
"Rangoli."

161
00:09:07,990 --> 00:09:09,620
These are designs used
to decorate the entrance.

162
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:12,090
Washing a guest's feet...

163
00:09:12,420 --> 00:09:14,760
is a traditional custom in our country
for welcoming honored guests.

164
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:17,760
Really?

165
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:22,930
For supposedly the best hotel in Korea,
the service is awful.

166
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:25,470
Especially you. You're the worst.

167
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:26,740
Let's go, Tommy.

168
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:31,140
Wait. No, please. It was my fault.
Let me wash your feet.

169
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:33,180
Please have a seat. Please, just sit...

170
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,850
The service at this hotel is a disgrace.

171
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,680
How revolting.

172
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:40,180
Is this really how you
welcome your guests?

173
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:42,790
Please forgive me. I was unprofessional.

174
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,260
Please give me another chance.

175
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:49,890
Thank you, Chairman.

176
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,560
Then wash my feet, now.

177
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,470
She's doing a great job.

178
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,770
But what if Chae Hwa Young catches on?

179
00:09:58,970 --> 00:10:00,940
I doubt it. She's too blinded by money.

180
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:02,570
She's desperate to secure this investment.

181
00:10:04,010 --> 00:10:08,050
Mom. You're really going through a lot.
I'll send Team Leader Jin over soon.

182
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:10,750
See you later, Baek Ho.

183
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,280
See you.

184
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,490
Team Leader Jin.

185
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:22,760
Go and see if Chae Hwa Young is attending
to Chairman Ali properly...

186
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:24,000
and not making any mistakes.

187
00:10:24,430 --> 00:10:26,130
And also check
if the Chairman needs anything.

188
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,400
Understood.

189
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:36,940
Just wait until I get this investment.
I won't let you off the hook.

190
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:40,140
No.

191
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:43,610
On your knees.
And use both hands, respectfully.

192
00:10:44,050 --> 00:10:45,650
Yes.

193
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:03,570
Chairman Ali, is everything alright?

194
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:08,010
Hey, I've got this under control,
so you can leave, Team Leader Jin.

195
00:11:08,770 --> 00:11:10,170
Oh, no!

196
00:11:11,340 --> 00:11:13,280
What's wrong now?

197
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,110
I feel so disgusted.

198
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:18,380
How bad a person are you?

199
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:22,550
The moment your hands touched my feet,
my skin crawled.

200
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:25,920
I feel so filthy.
Get them away from me, now!

201
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:27,960
Tommy, the bell.

202
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:29,260
Yes.

203
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:32,260
Here you go, Chairman.

204
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:42,110
- Begone, evil spirit!
- Don't move!

205
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:43,870
- Begone, evil spirit!
- It's a purification ritual.

206
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:48,110
- Run, and you'll be cursed for life.
- Evil spirit, be gone!

207
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:50,510
Seriously! Please, stop it!

208
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:56,450
You wretched woman.
Be gone, evil spirit! Be gone, demon!

209
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:58,190
- You wicked woman.
- I told you to stop!

210
00:11:58,490 --> 00:12:00,930
- Are you trying to drive me crazy?
- Be gone, evil spirit!

211
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,290
- Ali.
- Be gone, evil spirit!

212
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,790
Don't you dare back out of the investment.

213
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:07,500
I'll get that investment money from you
even if it kills me.

214
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,700
Be gone, evil spirit!

215
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:09,800
What?

216
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:13,770
Chae Hwa Young washed Chairman Ali's feet?
Seriously?

217
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,610
Yes, on her knees, too.

218
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:19,910
Word has already spread among the staff.

219
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:24,120
On top of that, it seemed she upset
Chairman Ali while washing her feet...

220
00:12:24,420 --> 00:12:28,950
because she was groveling at her feet,
begging for forgiveness.

221
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:31,560
- Is that really true?
- Instead of working,

222
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:34,630
are you all just wasting time gossiping?

223
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,930
No, I was just saying.

224
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:41,800
CEO Chae looked so pathetic
that it was embarrassing to watch.

225
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:44,400
But we have a professional concierge
for a reason.

226
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,770
I don't know why
she's bothering with this.

227
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:48,070
No one even asked her to.

228
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:51,080
Why she'd volunteer for such humiliation
is beyond me.

229
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:59,020
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

230
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,550
Chairman Ali...

231
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:04,360
I know she's an investor,
but this is just too much.

232
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:08,190
How can she make the CEO of a hotel
grovel like that?

233
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:10,030
That woman... Seriously...

234
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:14,930
Time for the final welcome.

235
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,100
What?

236
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,740
There's still more?

237
00:13:19,370 --> 00:13:21,270
I'm going to lose my mind!

238
00:13:21,870 --> 00:13:25,180
And why is that punk Tommy
so disrespectful to me?

239
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,850
He's obnoxious in so many ways.

240
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:29,450
Get on your knees...

241
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:32,520
and kiss Chairman Ali's feet
as if in worship.

242
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:34,050
What?

243
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:36,820
You want me to kiss her feet?

244
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:38,790
You don't want to?

245
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:40,860
- Let's go, Tommy.
- No, I'll do it!

246
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:42,190
I'll do it.

247
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:51,700
Hurry up. Quickly!

248
00:13:56,110 --> 00:14:00,040
Again. Like you mean it!

249
00:14:08,290 --> 00:14:10,920
Again. That was too short.

250
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:14,860
A sincere welcome, reverence.
Don't you get it?

251
00:14:14,930 --> 00:14:16,690
- You know?
- Yes...

252
00:14:26,870 --> 00:14:28,510
Are you taking pictures?

253
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:30,510
A memento.

254
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,620
What a spectacle.

255
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:44,660
My mom said she was always
in school plays when she was a kid.

256
00:14:44,890 --> 00:14:48,860
I can't get used to seeing Mom like this.
It feels like I'm in a dream.

257
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:51,400
I know, right? I feel the same way.

258
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:54,530
To think that because of Chae Hwa Young,

259
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:58,300
she spent all those years
without ever getting to truly blossom...

260
00:14:58,670 --> 00:15:01,110
- must be so infuriating for her.
- And that's not all.

261
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:04,710
She also lost Seo Rin.

262
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:09,010
And not only that, she lost Oh Bok Gil,
whom she adored like an older brother.

263
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:10,580
Can you imagine her
deep-seated resentment?

264
00:15:10,850 --> 00:15:14,120
And after my mom regained her sanity,
her shock must have been even greater.

265
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,920
Compared to all that suffering,

266
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:18,990
making Chae Hwa Young suffer like this
is letting her off easy.

267
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,390
Anyway, I just hope
Mom doesn't get caught.

268
00:15:23,930 --> 00:15:27,230
Right, Baek Ho.
We should get going to my grandfather's.

269
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:28,770
Right.

270
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:32,500
If we stop at the store for a gift,
we should get going.

271
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:38,710
Thank you for having me, Chairman.

272
00:15:38,780 --> 00:15:41,380
Of course.
I should have had you over sooner.

273
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:42,450
Come on in.

274
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:45,380
My goodness, what's all this?
You're just visiting your future in-laws.

275
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:46,880
What did you bring?

276
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,250
It's nothing special.

277
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:49,750
It's just some ginseng
and traditional sweets.

278
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:51,790
Oh my, you shouldn't have.

279
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,390
Still, I felt awkward coming empty-handed.

280
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:05,000
(Ma)

281
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:08,310
What is this?
I have no idea what that crest is.

282
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:13,410
You see, because of my
high blood pressure,

283
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,250
I can't eat the ginseng chicken soup.

284
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:19,850
I feel bad eating it by myself.
I wish you could join me, Chairman.

285
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:22,350
Don't worry, we're having some too.

286
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:25,820
That's right, Lawyer Kang.
Don't worry, and just enjoy it.

287
00:16:25,990 --> 00:16:28,060
Yes, go ahead and eat.

288
00:16:28,530 --> 00:16:30,460
All right, everyone. Let's eat.

289
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:35,470
(Ma)

290
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:38,300
Is that the same crest on my golden spoon?

291
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:40,700
No, it can't be.

292
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:50,510
Jang Mi, it looks like you haven't changed
Seo Rin's room at all.

293
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:52,350
It's just as I remember it.

294
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:54,790
Grandfather told me to redecorate,

295
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,790
but I like it this way.

296
00:16:57,590 --> 00:16:58,590
The truth is,

297
00:16:59,220 --> 00:17:00,920
I keep feeling like Seo Rin...

298
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:03,760
is going to walk through
that door and say,

299
00:17:04,460 --> 00:17:06,560
"What are you doing in my room? Shit."

300
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:09,630
Don't be so sad.

301
00:17:10,370 --> 00:17:12,100
We will get to the bottom of this,
no matter what.

302
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:16,110
And we'll make sure Seo Rin
can finally rest in peace.

303
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:19,180
Of course. We have to.

304
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,910
But, Baek Ho, is something wrong?

305
00:17:23,310 --> 00:17:25,220
No, nothing's wrong.

306
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,150
It's just, Jun Ho...

307
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:30,690
- Never mind.
- What? What is it?

308
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:33,820
What about Kang Jun Ho?
What did he say to you?

309
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,960
He was about to say something,

310
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:38,130
but I stopped him
and said I'd rather hear it from you.

311
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,130
Good call.

312
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,400
The thing is...

313
00:17:44,370 --> 00:17:45,400
The thing is what?

314
00:17:46,740 --> 00:17:47,770
Don't tell me, Baek Ho...

315
00:17:48,410 --> 00:17:50,010
You don't have some weird disease, do you?

316
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:52,240
Or is it another woman?

317
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,840
That's ridiculous.

318
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,580
Who do you think I am?
I'm a one-woman man.

319
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:58,750
The truth is...

320
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:02,590
My mom and dad...

321
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:04,520
are not my birth parents.

322
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:07,060
They adopted me.

323
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:09,430
- Just like Kang Jun Ho.
- What?

324
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:11,660
Then...

325
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:13,300
They adopted me when I was a baby...

326
00:18:13,730 --> 00:18:16,800
and adopted Kang Jun Ho later
when he was older.

327
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,540
This doesn't change how you feel about me,
does it?

328
00:18:20,740 --> 00:18:23,470
That's ridiculous.
Why would I ever think less of you?

329
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:24,880
What do you take me for?
I'm a one-man woman.

330
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,210
We're about to get married,

331
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:33,520
so let's be completely honest
with no more secrets.

332
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:36,050
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

333
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:38,720
All that matters is that I know now.

334
00:18:39,690 --> 00:18:43,190
But you don't happen to know
who your birth parents are, do you?

335
00:18:43,930 --> 00:18:46,330
No. And I have no desire to find them.

336
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:49,630
As far as I'm concerned,
Lawyer Han Young Ja is my only mother.

337
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,300
If you ever want to look for them,
let's do it together.

338
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:53,800
I'll help you.

339
00:19:07,890 --> 00:19:08,890
Right.

340
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:10,520
The crest.

341
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:16,060
(Ma)

342
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,500
(Ma)

343
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:25,200
I was right.
It was identical to this crest.

344
00:19:26,570 --> 00:19:30,270
They said this was with me
when I first came to the orphanage.

345
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:35,950
Baek Ho, you're home.

346
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,580
Mom, you're still up?

347
00:19:37,980 --> 00:19:41,990
You're so late.
Sounds like the Chairman treated you well.

348
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:44,120
The Chairman officially accepted me
as his son-in-law...

349
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:45,720
and even made me ginseng chicken soup.

350
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:47,290
Really?

351
00:19:47,990 --> 00:19:52,730
He really rolled out the red carpet
for you.

352
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:56,370
But why do you have this out?

353
00:19:57,170 --> 00:19:59,100
There's just something I needed to check.

354
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,240
By any chance,

355
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,810
did you hear anything
when you first brought me home?

356
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,280
About this golden toad or golden spoon.

357
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,480
I'm not sure.

358
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,250
Then...

359
00:20:11,780 --> 00:20:14,150
could you give me
the orphanage director's phone number?

360
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:17,790
Actually, I thought of that
after we spoke the other day.

361
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:21,660
I tried to call her,
but I think her number has changed.

362
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:22,990
I couldn't get through.

363
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:24,190
Really?

364
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:27,430
I'll find out for you one way or another.

365
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:29,670
Okay, thanks. I'm counting on you.

366
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:38,510
Are you just leaving now?

367
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:42,450
Take this and go to a snack bar nearby
and buy some tteokbokki, sundae,

368
00:20:42,450 --> 00:20:43,650
and some other things.

369
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:46,180
What? Tteokbokki at this hour?

370
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:50,150
She watched a drama and wants me to get it
from the place she saw on the show.

371
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:52,020
That's all the way over
by Gangnam Station.

372
00:20:52,390 --> 00:20:53,860
That's a 90-minute round trip.

373
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:56,660
The tteokbokki will be
a soggy mess by then.

374
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:59,130
Besides, it's not like she'd know
the difference.

375
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,200
Just tell them to throw it
in a plastic bag.

376
00:21:01,730 --> 00:21:02,930
I can't risk getting caught over this.

377
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:05,970
- It'll be a huge headache. Hurry.
- Yes, ma'am.

378
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,470
Try to get some rest while I'm gone.

379
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,580
Just you wait, Ali, you witch.

380
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:20,880
Never have I been so humiliated
on someone's power trip.

381
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:23,750
And to be utterly humiliated
in front of Team Leader Jin.

382
00:21:24,790 --> 00:21:25,820
I'm so pissed off.

383
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,660
I've never had such a difficult day.

384
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,910
Yes, Chairman Ali. I'm on my way
to get the tteokbokki...

385
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:49,380
Hurry up. Get back here, right now.

386
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:51,280
But I'm already near Gangnam Station...

387
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:54,990
Shut up. I know you didn't go.

388
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:56,990
- What?
- Get back here now.

389
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:58,690
- Yes.
- Now.

390
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:02,430
How did she find out?

391
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:05,860
Ma'am, I'm back with the tteokbokki.

392
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,200
Ma'am, I bought this for you.

393
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:16,740
Are you out of your mind?

394
00:22:17,910 --> 00:22:19,580
Why are you doing this to me?

395
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:22,080
I went all the way
to Gangnam Station to get this for you.

396
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,350
Why are you so angry with me?

397
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:25,950
You resort to violence
over every little thing.

398
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:27,920
You think you've been wronged?

399
00:22:28,450 --> 00:22:29,450
Look at this.

400
00:22:33,860 --> 00:22:36,490
Tommy took this picture for me.

401
00:22:36,830 --> 00:22:40,460
It's so far,
so I had Tommy go check it out.

402
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,330
Where were you?

403
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:47,400
We must have just missed each other.

404
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:50,010
You're lying.

405
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:52,910
I'm not lying, Chairman.

406
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:54,280
Out!

407
00:22:55,210 --> 00:22:58,580
You're a liar. You're out!

408
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:02,020
I'm checking out tomorrow.
You can have it.

409
00:23:02,290 --> 00:23:03,390
Get out now!

410
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:05,520
Shit.

411
00:23:08,990 --> 00:23:12,630
Unbelievable! Ali!

412
00:23:13,530 --> 00:23:15,400
That crazy woman thinks
she can work me like a dog?

413
00:23:16,570 --> 00:23:18,400
What a massive pain.

414
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,740
And now she's threatening
to leave the hotel again?

415
00:23:22,070 --> 00:23:23,540
She's impossible!

416
00:23:24,340 --> 00:23:27,410
Fine! This is too degrading.
Forget the investment!

417
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:28,550
Tell her the deal's off!

418
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:35,890
Hey, Jun Ho.

419
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:37,750
I heard what happened from the Director.

420
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:39,390
Are you holding up okay?

421
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:41,660
Oh, my son.

422
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:43,860
You called because you were
worried about me.

423
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:48,500
I've dealt with my fair share
of nightmare clients before,

424
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,500
but she really takes the cake.

425
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:53,440
Just drop the deal with Chairman Ali.

426
00:23:54,370 --> 00:23:57,370
I hate seeing you swallow your pride
and bow down to her like that.

427
00:23:57,940 --> 00:24:00,280
I'll find other investors,
so please, just stop.

428
00:24:00,340 --> 00:24:02,910
No. It's not that easy to find an investor
of her caliber.

429
00:24:04,050 --> 00:24:06,180
Who else would invest that much in us?

430
00:24:10,220 --> 00:24:11,690
I don't have the energy
to talk to you right now.

431
00:24:12,290 --> 00:24:13,560
What happened?

432
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,990
Chairman Ali called me,
and she was absolutely furious.

433
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:17,990
Let's talk about it tomorrow.

434
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:23,330
Chairman Ali said she's too exhausted,
so she's staying at our hotel tonight.

435
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:26,970
I'll find a way to win her over tomorrow,
so don't worry and just go.

436
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:29,770
First thing tomorrow morning,
you need to book a nail artist...

437
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:32,440
and send them to Chairman Ali's room
by 9:30 a.m.

438
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:34,440
And tell the staff to prepare
anything else she needs.

439
00:24:35,150 --> 00:24:38,320
How am I supposed to find a nail artist
that early in the morning?

440
00:24:38,380 --> 00:24:41,720
That's all up to you.
You said you could handle it.

441
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:45,120
Fine, I'll take care of it.

442
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:49,760
I've seen arrogance,
but this world-class arrogance is a first.

443
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:53,960
Take good care of her tomorrow.
No more mistakes.

444
00:24:54,330 --> 00:24:55,330
Please.

445
00:25:03,110 --> 00:25:04,110
Mom.

446
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:05,810
Jang Mi.

447
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:18,960
Mom, you had a really rough day,
didn't you?

448
00:25:19,990 --> 00:25:23,090
Thanks to this,
I really had Chae Hwa Young fooled.

449
00:25:23,490 --> 00:25:26,260
But I doubt she'll keep falling for it.

450
00:25:26,530 --> 00:25:30,000
Either way, Chae Hwa Young is focused
on securing that investment right now,

451
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:32,000
so she won't suspect you.

452
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,400
I just need you for one more day, Mom.

453
00:25:35,370 --> 00:25:38,640
It was satisfying to make
Chae Hwa Young suffer,

454
00:25:40,010 --> 00:25:42,850
but it's nothing compared to
what she put me through.

455
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:09,770
I can't risk leaving it at home.

456
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:12,610
I need to hide it somewhere else.

457
00:26:24,990 --> 00:26:25,990
What's this?

458
00:26:26,060 --> 00:26:30,030
When I met Chairman Ma 30 years ago,
while pregnant with Dong Seok's child,

459
00:26:30,330 --> 00:26:32,560
Chairman Ma gave it to me.
You remember, right?

460
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:33,860
Yes.

461
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:35,470
Of course, I remember.

462
00:26:35,730 --> 00:26:37,230
Here's the key. Go on, open it.

463
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:51,820
This is...

464
00:26:51,820 --> 00:26:54,420
I don't trust Oh Jang Mi,
so I brought it here.

465
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:57,320
That brat will get into my drawers
one way or another.

466
00:26:58,220 --> 00:27:02,360
I want you to keep Seo Rin's baby clothes
and this necklace hidden for a while.

467
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:04,960
Yes.

468
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:06,860
I'm counting on you.

469
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:11,300
And don't get any ideas
about siding with Han Young Ja to test me.

470
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:17,240
By the way, something has been
bothering me for a long time.

471
00:27:17,810 --> 00:27:22,110
When Father gave this to me,
there were two golden toads, right?

472
00:27:23,150 --> 00:27:26,120
But back then, when I moved
into the Chairman's house with Seo Rin,

473
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:27,980
I didn't get a chance
to grab this until later.

474
00:27:28,550 --> 00:27:32,990
I was so busy with Seo Rin and Chairman Ma
that I didn't check it until later.

475
00:27:33,620 --> 00:27:36,260
But one of the golden toads was missing,
and I couldn't find it anywhere.

476
00:28:06,620 --> 00:28:08,120
(The First Man)

477
00:28:08,190 --> 00:28:10,390
Bring Kang Jun Ho to the lobby right now.

478
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:12,400
Take off those leather shoes, now.

479
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:15,130
Have you no respect for our traditions?

480
00:28:15,330 --> 00:28:19,000
Chae Hwa Young, your 30 years
in this business really show.

481
00:28:19,140 --> 00:28:21,240
- Is that supposed to be sarcasm?
- It is.

482
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:25,040
- What did you say?
- Chae Hwa Young. You need to suffer more.

483
00:28:25,110 --> 00:28:26,140
What's wrong?

484
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:28,680
I think Chairman Ali is Jung Suk Hee!

485
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:30,850
She must have gotten her memory back.

486
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,920
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
